data.sem <- 
    data.ch |>

# run resampling
set.seed(74)
coef.sem <- replicate(1000, {
  slice_sample(data.sem, n = 32, replace = TRUE) |>
    unnest(cols = c(data)) |>
    group_by(condition, selection) |>    
    summarize(mprop = mean(sprop), .groups = "drop")        
}, simplify = FALSE)  

# data frame with sem
bound.sem <- coef.sem |>
  bind_rows(.id = "iteration") |> 
  select(condition, selection, mprop) |>
  group_by(condition, selection) |>
  summarize(
    sem_low = mean(mprop) + sd(mprop),
    sem_upp = mean(mprop) - sd(mprop),
    .groups = "drop"  # Drop grouping
  )

Inferential for Choice

# recode variables
df.choice <-
  data.ch |>
    mutate(
    c.speaker = as.numeric(ifelse(speaker == "SpeakerA", -.5, .5)),
    c.group = as.numeric(ifelse(group == "Experimental", -.5, .5)))


# test lmer
model <- glmer(choice ~ c.speaker*c.group +  
                 (1|subjid) + (1|itemid), df.choice, na.action=na.omit,
               family=binomial, control=glmerControl(optimizer="bobyqa"))

Online measures: eye-tracking

###Descriptives eye-tracking ####Prepare data frames: aggregate by subjects, intepolate and smoothing

# data aggregated by subjid less window from 0 to 3000ms
data1.eye.e1 <- 
  data0.eye.e1 |>
    filter(bin <= 10) |>
    group_by(subjid, group, speaker, msbin) |>
    summarize(mpnew = mean(pnew),
            mpold = mean(pold),
            mpblank = mean(pblank), .groups = "drop") |>
    select(subjid, group, speaker, ms = msbin, mpnew, mpold, mpblank)


# interpolation (linear) and smoothing (LOESS)
data2.eye.e1 <- 
  data1.eye.e1 |>
  arrange(subjid, group, speaker, ms) |>
  group_by(subjid, group, speaker) |>  
  complete(ms = seq(min(ms, na.rm = TRUE), max(ms, na.rm = TRUE), by = 50)) |> 
  arrange(ms) |>  # Ensure sorted bin values
  mutate(
    newi = approx(x = ms, y = mpnew, xout = ms, method = "linear")$y,
    oldi = approx(x = ms, y = mpold, xout = ms, method = "linear")$y,
    blanki = approx(x = ms, y = mpblank, xout = ms, method = "linear")$y) |> 
  ungroup() |> 
  group_by(subjid, group, speaker) |>
  arrange(subjid, group, speaker, ms) |>
  mutate(
    newis = {
      fit <- loess(newi ~ ms, data = cur_data(), span = 1.4)
      predict(fit, ms)},
    oldis = { 
      fit <- loess(oldi ~ ms, data = cur_data(), span = 1.4)
      predict(fit, ms)},
    blankis = { 
      fit <- loess(blanki ~ ms, data = cur_data(), span = 1.4)
      predict(fit, ms)},
    diffis = newis - oldis) |>
  ungroup()

Bootstrap subjects for Standar Error by object and condition

# nesting data
data2.nest.prop.e1 <- 
  data2.eye.e1 |>
  filter(!is.na(mpnew)) |> 
  select(subjid, group, speaker, ms, new = newis, old = oldis, blank = blankis, diff = diffis) |>
  pivot_longer(cols = c("new", "old", "blank", "diff"), names_to = "obj", values_to = "ps") |>
  arrange(subjid, group, speaker, obj, ms) |>
  nest(data = -c("subjid","group")) |>
  arrange(group)


# run the randomization experimental condition
set.seed(74)
coef.eyeE <- replicate(1000, {
  dataE <- data2.nest.prop.e1 |> filter(group == "Experimental")
  slice_sample(dataE, n = 16, replace = TRUE) |>
    unnest(cols = c(data)) |>
    group_by(speaker, obj, ms) |>    
    summarize(mps = mean(ps),
              .groups = "drop")}, simplify = FALSE)  

# extract from large list experimental group
bounds.eyeE <- 
  coef.eyeE |>
  bind_rows(.id = "iteration") |> 
  select(speaker, obj, ms,  mps) |>  # Explicitly keep only required columns
  group_by(speaker, obj, ms) |>
  summarize(
    lower = mean(mps) + sd(mps),
    upper = mean(mps) - sd(mps),
    .groups = "drop") |>
  arrange(speaker, obj, ms) 

# data frame with real data experimental group
realm.eyeE <-
  data2.eye.e1 |>
  filter(group == "Experimental", !is.na(mpnew)) |>
  group_by(speaker, ms) |>
  summarise(
    new = mean(mpnew),
    old = mean(mpold),
    blank = mean(mpblank),
    diff = mean(mpnew - mpold),
    .groups = "drop") |>
  pivot_longer(cols = c("new", "old", "blank", "diff"), names_to = "obj", values_to = "preal") |>
  arrange(speaker, obj, ms)

# data frame with real data points and se by bootstrap experimental group
real.boundsE <- 
  realm.eyeE |>
  inner_join(bounds.eyeE,
             by=c("speaker", "obj", "ms")) |>
  mutate(group = "Experimental")

data frames for stats cluster

data2.eye.e1.r <- 
data2.eye.e1 |>
    mutate(
    c.speaker = case_when(
      speaker %in% c("SpeakerA") ~ "-.5",
      speaker %in% c("SpeakerB") ~ ".5"),    
  c.group = case_when(
      group %in% c("Experimental" ) ~ "-.5",
      group %in% c("Control") ~ ".5"),
  c.speaker = as.numeric(c.speaker),
  c.group = as.numeric(c.group))

data.to0 <- 
  data2.eye.e1.r |>
  filter(ms >= 0, ms <=3000) |>
  select(subjid, c.group, c.speaker, ms, diffis) |>
  arrange(subjid, c.group, c.speaker, ms) |>
  nest(data = -c("subjid", "c.group")) |>
  arrange(subjid)

find clusters in participant’s data

# find cluster in real data
data.real <- 
  data.to0 |>
  unnest(cols = c(data)) |>
    ungroup()

cluster.real0 <-
  data.real |> 
  group_by(ms) |> 
  summarise(
    model = list(lm(diffis ~ c.speaker * c.group, data = cur_data())), 
    .groups = "drop"
  ) |> 
  mutate(
    model_summary = map(model, tidy) 
  ) |> 
  unnest(model_summary) |>
  select(ms, term, estimate, statistic, p.value) |>  
  mutate(
    sig = ifelse(p.value >= 0.05, 0, 1)
  ) |> 
  group_by(term) |>  
  mutate(
    cluster = cumsum(
      sig != lag(sig, default = first(sig)) | 
      sign(statistic) != lag(sign(statistic), default = sign(first(statistic)))
    )
  ) |>
  group_by(cluster, sig, term) |> 
  summarise(
    start_ms = min(ms),
    end_ms = max(ms),
    n_ms = n(),
    mean_value = mean(statistic),
    sum_value = sum(statistic),
    .groups = "drop"
  ) |>
  arrange(term) |>
  filter(sig==1)

Cluster permutation (only for the intercept)

# data frame and variables for resampling
nsubj <- data.to0 |> distinct(subjid) |> count() |> pull()
set.seed(78)

# resampling
coef.reg <- replicate(10000, {

  data.to <- data.to0 |>
    shuffle(c.group) |>
    unnest(cols = c(data)) |> ungroup()
  
data.to |> 
  group_by(ms) |> 
  summarize(
    t_value = map_dbl(
      .x = list(cur_data()), 
      ~ summary(lm(diffis ~ c.speaker * c.group, data = .x))$coefficients["(Intercept)", "t value"]
    )
  )  

}, simplify = FALSE)


# get data 
dist1 <- coef.reg |> bind_rows(.id = "iteration")

# pivot wide
dist2 <-
  dist1 |> 
   select(iteration, ms, t_value) |>
    pivot_wider(names_from = iteration, values_from = t_value)


## Recode based on quantile
# Extract ms column separately
ms_col <- dist2$ms

# Convert to matrix for efficiency (excluding ms column)
dist_matrix <- as.matrix(dist2[ , !names(dist2) %in% "ms"])

# Compute row-wise quantiles efficiently
q95 <- apply(dist_matrix, 1, quantile, probs = 0.95)
q05 <- apply(dist_matrix, 1, quantile, probs = 0.05)

# Apply conditions using matrix operations
flags_matrix <- (dist_matrix > q95) - (dist_matrix < q05)

# Convert back to data frame
flags <- as.data.frame(flags_matrix)

# Insert ms as the first column
flags <- cbind(ms = ms_col, flags)


# Convert to data.table
flags_dt <- as.data.table(flags)


## Find clusters in permuted dataset 
# Reshape to long format efficiently (process in chunks if necessary)
clusters_dt <- melt(flags_dt, id.vars = "ms", variable.name = "column", value.name = "value", verbose = FALSE)

# Convert column names to character for consistency
clusters_dt[, column := as.character(column)]

# Compute cluster IDs 
clusters_dt[, cluster := cumsum(value != shift(value, type = "lag", fill = first(value))), by = column]

# Summarize clusters 
clusters <- clusters_dt[, .(
  start_ms = first(ms),
  end_ms = last(ms),
  n_points = .N
), by = .(column, cluster, value)]

# Convert `dist2` to `data.table` 
dist2_dt <- as.data.table(dist2)

# Reduce memory by selecting only relevant columns
dist2_dt <- dist2_dt[, c("ms", unique(clusters$column)), with = FALSE]

# Process sum_abs_values in **chunks** to avoid memory overload
batch_size <- 500  # Adjust this based on available RAM
unique_columns <- unique(clusters$column)
sum_abs_values_list <- list()

for (i in seq(1, length(unique_columns), by = batch_size)) {
  batch_cols <- unique_columns[i:min(i + batch_size - 1, length(unique_columns))]
  
  # Filter relevant data for the batch
  batch_dist2 <- dist2_dt[, c("ms", batch_cols), with = FALSE]

  # Compute sum of absolute values efficiently in batches
  batch_sums <- clusters[column %in% batch_cols, .(
    sum_abs_values = sum(abs(batch_dist2[ms %between% c(start_ms, end_ms), get(column)]), na.rm = TRUE)
  ), by = .(column, cluster)]
  
  sum_abs_values_list[[length(sum_abs_values_list) + 1]] <- batch_sums
}

# Combine batch results
sum_abs_values <- rbindlist(sum_abs_values_list)

# Merge results back into `clusters`
clusters <- merge(clusters, sum_abs_values, by = c("column", "cluster"), all.x = TRUE)


# get distribution
mass.st0.e1 <- 
  clusters |>
    ungroup() |>
    filter(value != 0) |>
    group_by(column) |>
    arrange(column, desc(sum_abs_values)) |>
    slice(1) |>
    pull(sum_abs_values)

# save
dist1.int <- dist1
clusters.int <- clusters
mass.st0.int <- mass.st0.e1
saveRDS(dist1.int, "./data/coef.clusters.int.e1.rds")
saveRDS(clusters.int, "./data/clusters.int.e1.rds")
saveRDS(mass.st0.int, "./data/distmass.int.e1.rds")

Inferential by item on-line: eye-tracking

####Prepare data frames by item I

# data aggregated by itemid less window from 0 to 3000ms
data1.eye.e1i <- 
  data0.eye.e1 |>
    filter(bin <= 10) |>
    group_by(itemid, group, speaker, msbin) |>
    summarize(mpnew = mean(pnew),
            mpold = mean(pold),
            mpblank = mean(pblank), .groups = "drop") |>
    select(itemid, group, speaker, ms = msbin, mpnew, mpold, mpblank)


# interpolation (linear) and smoothing (LOESS)
data2.eye.e1i <- 
  data1.eye.e1i |>
  arrange(itemid, group, speaker, ms) |>
  group_by(itemid, group, speaker) |>  
  complete(ms = seq(min(ms, na.rm = TRUE), max(ms, na.rm = TRUE), by = 50)) |> 
  arrange(ms) |>  # Ensure sorted bin values
  mutate(
    newi = approx(x = ms, y = mpnew, xout = ms, method = "linear")$y,
    oldi = approx(x = ms, y = mpold, xout = ms, method = "linear")$y,
    blanki = approx(x = ms, y = mpblank, xout = ms, method = "linear")$y) |> 
  ungroup() |> 
  group_by(itemid, group, speaker) |>
  arrange(itemid, group, speaker, ms) |>
  mutate(
    newis = {
      fit <- loess(newi ~ ms, data = cur_data(), span = 1.4)
      predict(fit, ms)},
    oldis = { 
      fit <- loess(oldi ~ ms, data = cur_data(), span = 1.4)
      predict(fit, ms)},
    blankis = { 
      fit <- loess(blanki ~ ms, data = cur_data(), span = 1.4)
      predict(fit, ms)},
    diffis = newis - oldis) |>
  ungroup()

####Prepare data frames by item II

data2.eye.e1.ri <- 
data2.eye.e1i |>
    mutate(
    c.speaker = case_when(
      speaker %in% c("SpeakerA") ~ "-.5",
      speaker %in% c("SpeakerB") ~ ".5"),    
  c.group = case_when(
      group %in% c("Experimental" ) ~ "-.5",
      group %in% c("Control") ~ ".5"),
  c.speaker = as.numeric(c.speaker),
  c.group = as.numeric(c.group))

data.to0i <- 
  data2.eye.e1.ri |>
  filter(ms >= 0, ms <=3000) |>
  select(itemid, c.group, c.speaker, ms, diffis) |>
  arrange(itemid, c.group, c.speaker, ms) |>
  nest(data = -c("itemid", "c.group")) |>
  arrange(itemid)

Find clusters in participant’s data by item

# find cluster in real data
data.reali <- 
  data.to0i |>
  unnest(cols = c(data)) |>
    ungroup()

cluster.real0i <-
  data.reali |> 
  group_by(ms) |> 
  summarise(
    model = list(lm(diffis ~ c.speaker * c.group, data = cur_data())), 
    .groups = "drop"
  ) |> 
  mutate(
    model_summary = map(model, tidy) 
  ) |> 
  unnest(model_summary) |>
  select(ms, term, estimate, statistic, p.value) |>  
  mutate(
    sig = ifelse(p.value >= 0.05, 0, 1)
  ) |> 
  group_by(term) |>  
  mutate(
    cluster = cumsum(
      sig != lag(sig, default = first(sig)) | 
      sign(statistic) != lag(sign(statistic), default = sign(first(statistic)))
    )
  ) |>
  group_by(cluster, sig, term) |> 
  summarise(
    start_ms = min(ms),
    end_ms = max(ms),
    n_ms = n(),
    mean_value = mean(statistic),
    sum_value = sum(statistic),
    .groups = "drop"
  ) |>
  arrange(term) |>
  filter(sig==1)

Cluster permutation (only for the intercept) by item

# data frame and variables for resampling
nitem <- data.to0i |> distinct(itemid) |> count() |> pull()
set.seed(78)

# resampling
coef.regi <- replicate(10000, {

  data.to <- data.to0i |>
    shuffle(c.group) |>
    unnest(cols = c(data)) |> ungroup()
  
data.to |> 
  group_by(ms) |> 
  summarize(
    t_value = map_dbl(
      .x = list(cur_data()), 
      ~ summary(lm(diffis ~ c.speaker * c.group, data = .x))$coefficients["(Intercept)", "t value"]
    )
  )  

}, simplify = FALSE)


# get data 
dist1i <- coef.regi |> bind_rows(.id = "iteration")

# pivot wide
dist2 <-
  dist1i |> 
   select(iteration, ms, t_value) |>
    pivot_wider(names_from = iteration, values_from = t_value)


## Recode based on quantile
# Extract ms column separately
ms_col <- dist2$ms

# Convert to matrix for efficiency (excluding ms column)
dist_matrix <- as.matrix(dist2[ , !names(dist2) %in% "ms"])

# Compute row-wise quantiles efficiently
q95 <- apply(dist_matrix, 1, quantile, probs = 0.95)
q05 <- apply(dist_matrix, 1, quantile, probs = 0.05)

# Apply conditions using matrix operations
flags_matrix <- (dist_matrix > q95) - (dist_matrix < q05)

# Convert back to data frame
flags <- as.data.frame(flags_matrix)

# Insert ms as the first column
flags <- cbind(ms = ms_col, flags)


# Convert to data.table
flags_dt <- as.data.table(flags)


## Find clusters in permuted dataset 
# Reshape to long format efficiently (process in chunks if necessary)
clusters_dt <- melt(flags_dt, id.vars = "ms", variable.name = "column", value.name = "value", verbose = FALSE)

# Convert column names to character for consistency
clusters_dt[, column := as.character(column)]

# Compute cluster IDs 
clusters_dt[, cluster := cumsum(value != shift(value, type = "lag", fill = first(value))), by = column]

# Summarize clusters 
clusters <- clusters_dt[, .(
  start_ms = first(ms),
  end_ms = last(ms),
  n_points = .N
), by = .(column, cluster, value)]

# Convert `dist2` to `data.table` 
dist2_dt <- as.data.table(dist2)

# Reduce memory by selecting only relevant columns
dist2_dt <- dist2_dt[, c("ms", unique(clusters$column)), with = FALSE]

# Process sum_abs_values in **chunks** to avoid memory overload
batch_size <- 500  # Adjust this based on available RAM
unique_columns <- unique(clusters$column)
sum_abs_values_list <- list()

for (i in seq(1, length(unique_columns), by = batch_size)) {
  batch_cols <- unique_columns[i:min(i + batch_size - 1, length(unique_columns))]
  
  # Filter relevant data for the batch
  batch_dist2 <- dist2_dt[, c("ms", batch_cols), with = FALSE]

  # Compute sum of absolute values efficiently in batches
  batch_sums <- clusters[column %in% batch_cols, .(
    sum_abs_values = sum(abs(batch_dist2[ms %between% c(start_ms, end_ms), get(column)]), na.rm = TRUE)
  ), by = .(column, cluster)]
  
  sum_abs_values_list[[length(sum_abs_values_list) + 1]] <- batch_sums
}

# Combine batch results
sum_abs_values <- rbindlist(sum_abs_values_list)

# Merge results back into `clusters`
clustersi <- merge(clusters, sum_abs_values, by = c("column", "cluster"), all.x = TRUE)


# get distribution
mass.st0.e1i <- 
  clustersi |>
    ungroup() |>
    filter(value != 0) |>
    group_by(column) |>
    arrange(column, desc(sum_abs_values)) |>
    slice(1) |>
    pull(sum_abs_values)

# save
dist1.inti <- dist1i
clusters.inti <- clustersi
mass.st0.inti <- mass.st0.e1i
saveRDS(dist1.inti, "./data/coef.clusters.int.e1i.rds")
saveRDS(clusters.inti, "./data/clusters.int.e1i.rds")
saveRDS(mass.st0.inti, "./data/distmass.int.e1i.rds")
